divine /dɪˈvaɪn/

1. ADJ You use divine to describe something that is provided by or relates to a god or goddess. 神的; 神圣的 

例： He suggested that the civil war had been a divine punishment. 他暗示此次内战是上天的惩罚。 

2. divinely ADV 如神般地; 神圣地 

例： The law was divinely ordained. 此法律为神授。 

3. ADJ People use divine to express their pleasure or enjoyment of something. 极好的; 绝妙的 

例： Her carrot cake is divine. 她的胡萝卜饼好吃极了。

</div>

